cs.IR, cs.DB, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.CR 

The paper discusses the design and development of a web search engine, which falls under the category of Information Retrieval (cs.IR). The engine's index is based on a DBMS, which suggests that it also falls under the category of Databases (cs.DB). The paper also mentions advanced Greek language stemming and real-time result clustering, which are techniques used in Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), respectively. Finally, the paper mentions advanced link analysis techniques for spam page detection, which falls under the category of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR).
